# Methodology — $event_label ($event_date) SFINCS reproduction

Generated by the `sfincs-flood-reproduction` skill on $build_date.
Pipeline: HydroMT-SFINCS + ERA5 + Copernicus DEM 30 m + ESA WorldCover
+ Copernicus EMS validation (rain-on-grid only).

## Event window

| Parameter | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Event date (EMS activation) | $event_date | from $ems_label |
| `tref`  | $tref | spin-up reference time ($spinup_days d before tstart) |
| `tstart` | $tstart | $pre_event_days d **before** the activation |
| `tstop`  | $tstop | $post_event_days d **after** the activation |
| Simulation length | $window_days d | $n_frames hourly output frames |

## Spatial setup

| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Lat/lon bbox | $south °N – $north °N, $west °E – $east °E |
| UTM zone | EPSG:$epsg |
| Grid | $ny × $nx cells at $res m ($total_cells base cells; $active_cells active) |
| Subgrid | $subgrid_pixels × $subgrid_pixels sub-pixels (effective $effective_res m) |
| UTM extent | $utm_extent |
| `zmin`, `zmax` (active mask) | -2 m, 250 m |
| `fill_area`, `drop_area` | 20 km², 5 km² |
| Boundary type | water-level (`zmax: 0`) — clip to sea level |

## Forcing

| Source | Variable | Time | Spatial |
|---|---|---|---|
| ERA5 (CDS, `reanalysis-era5-single-levels`) | `total_precipitation` (+ winds, MSLP) | hourly, $tref → $tstop | 0.25° grid over $south_buf-$north_buf N, $west_buf-$east_buf E |
| GloFAS v4.0 reanalysis (EWDS, `cems-glofas-historical`) | `river_discharge_in_the_last_24_hours` | daily | 0.05° grid (same bbox + buffer) |
| Copernicus DEM 30 m | elevation | static | $dem_tile_count tiles ($dem_tile_list) |
| ESA WorldCover 10 m | land-use class → Manning n | static, 2021 epoch | $worldcover_tile_count tile(s); $worldcover_vrt_note |

ERA5 `tp` is converted from m/h to mm/h. The CDS endpoint returned a ZIP
wrapper (accum + instant streams), unpacked + merged in `prep_inputs.py`.
GloFAS uses the EWDS endpoint (`https://ewds.climate.copernicus.eu/api`)
with the same CDS credential.

