## Caveats

1. **Rain-on-grid only** — no upstream Q boundary. The animation should
   be read as a **terrain + low-lying-area exposure** view with the EMS
   observed-flood polygons as ground truth, not as a calibrated flood
   forecast.
2. **DEM-driven bathy artefacts in reservoir / lake basins** — the DEM
   stores impounded water surfaces as nominal terrain, so the modelled
   depth can spike in lake cells. The relevant signal is the floodplain
   extent downstream, not the in-lake numbers.
3. **EMS observation gaps** — different MONIT iterations are acquired at
   different times; the merged observed-flood polygon set is the union of
   all monitorings.

